snippet.textDisplay:
@Rinkoo Kukreja only internet rumors think it's an engineered virus vs process of virus mutation like other viruses.

A PhD biologist channel also explained that viruses, like other life (a virus doesn't have a cell so most experts don't define it as alive, it's kinda borderline living), seek to *replicate themselves into the future* . Basic Darwin's evolution and experience hints that virus mutations that become more successful in spreading around and into the future, they typically become *less deadly* over time, because the more deadly forms kill the host and the virus dies off. That's why the *common cold virus* (which can be a rhinovirus or maybe other form of coronavirus) is *common* .. it's so mild that we just accept it and spread it without expending huge resources to stomp it out.
